er 1 piece","497 kJ \/ 119 kcal","2 g","15.7 g","5.4 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["This recipe is a great way to use up leftover mashed potato. Begin at step 3 with cold mashed potatoes.","Farl literally means ‘fourths’, as the dough is formed into a circle and then quartered. These Irish potato griddle cakes can be served with breakfast as an alternative to fried bread or hash browns, or they’re equally delicious spread with butter and served as an accompaniment to a bowl of hot soup."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 10m","8 pieces"]}